CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, August 22, 1956, pg. 1, reads: "Mother of Five Must Live in House With Leaky Roof, Falling Plaster - You Can See Outside - Anybody can look right outside through the holes between the walls where this plaster fell off in condemned home of Mrs. Shirley Brock and her five children, all on Mother's Assistance. The house has been condemned in order to build an addition to Terrace Village Housing Project, but there is no place available to which Mrs. Brock can move. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Kitchen wall with missing plaster, in condemned home of Shirley Brock, 424 Grove Street, Hill District
